---
By: Sextus, the Pythagorean
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 434
    Verse: 13
Tags:
  - Smile
---
God, indeed, is not in want of anything, but the wise man is in want of God
alone. He therefore, who is in want of few things, and those necessary,
emulates him who is in want of nothing.
